data.name: Savory Black Bean and Sweet Potato Chili
data.quickTastyDescription: A hearty chili packed with protein from black beans and flavor from sweet potatoes, perfect for a cozy dinner.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a pot, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add chopped onion and garlic; saut√© until translucent.
Add diced red bell pepper and cubed sweet potatoes. Cook for about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cumin and chili powder, cooking until fragrant, about 1 minute.
Add canned black beans (drained and rinsed), diced tomatoes, and vegetable broth. Bring to a simmer.
Reduce heat to low and let simmer for about 30 minutes, until sweet potatoes are tender. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot, garnished with fresh cilantro if desired.
